# Key Decisions & Tradeoffs

## Focus on Experience Orchestration Rather Than Capability Design

Capability design was owned by separate workstreams.

My focus remained on how customers moved between capabilities and experienced the journey as a whole.

### Tradeoff

Rather than redesigning individual services, I focused on improving how customers navigated between them.

---

## Optimize Notification Relevance Rather Than Notification Volume

Increasing communication frequency risked creating noise without improving confidence.

### Tradeoff

Fewer notifications.

Higher relevance and stronger signal quality.

---

## Design for Goals Rather Than Individual Requests

Customers think in outcomes rather than isolated interactions.

### Tradeoff

Increased orchestration complexity.

Improved continuity and reduced effort.

---

## Improve Confidence Before Optimizing Automation

Analysis suggested that transparency and predictability were prerequisites for effective automation.

### Tradeoff

Short-term focus on trust and clarity.

Long-term foundation for scalable automation.

